
<item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-boutros-mpls-tp-fault-02.txt'>
    <title>"MPLS-TP Fault OAM", Sami Boutros, Siva Sivabalan, George Swallow, David Ward, Stewart Bryant</title>
    <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-boutros-mpls-tp-fault-02.txt</link>
    <description>This draft specifies a fault management indications for MPLS Transport Profile(MPLS-TP) Label Switched Paths (LSPs).  The notification mechanism employs a generic method for a Maintenance End Point (MEP) or Maintenance Intermediate Point (MIP) to indicate a fault on an MPLS-TP LSP.  A new MPLS Operation, Administration, and Maintenance (OAM) message is defined.</description>
    <dc:date>2009-07-12T22:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
</item>
